records.addlTxt:
Defendant Marquise Z Mayes in court with Attorney Thomas Evangelos Harris.  Hanna Ritchie Kolberg for Antonella Aleman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Matter here for sentencing.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  AS TO COUNT #1:  The Court imposed the following sentence: The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be SEVEN (7) years.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for FOUR (4) years with credit for SEVENTY-NINE (79) days time served.  Defendant shall serve THREE (3) years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  The Court STAYED the matter and orders probation for FOUR (4) years.

AS TO COUNT #2:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve SIXTY (60) DAYS in the House of Correction CONCURRENT to count #1.
  
The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program;
The defendant is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court advised the defendant of the determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess any gun or other firearms. 
Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.  

Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Random urine screens to ensure compliance;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Serve ONE (1) year in the House of Correction, STRAIGHT TIME, no good time.
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements by the end of probationary period.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.   

